cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI 

This paper proposes a new framework for interpreting the effects of fairness criteria in machine learning. It focuses on the societal welfare and distributional impacts of classification assignments, which are central concerns of distributive justice. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
